main event: Five TACA crew members reported sighting four disc-shaped objects over Guatemala City Airport on March 15, 1950.
interesting points: The objects were described as dull silver and appeared larger than a T-33 aircraft., The crew reported the objects as flying silently at approximately 25,000 feet., The sighting lasted for an estimated duration of 3-4 minutes., The objects were observed in a single formation moving northwards over the airport., No vapor trails or engine noise were noted during the sighting.
sighted object: four disc-shaped objects in the sky
witness description: TACA crew members including the pilot, engineer, and co-pilot
